Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Bring a large #saucepan{} of water with @salt{1/2%tsp} to the boil. Remove the @puff pastry sheet{3/4} from your fridge.

Chop the @baking potato{1} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel).

When boiling, add the potatoes to the water and cook until you can easily slip a knife through, ~{15-20%minutes}. Once cooked, carefully drain in a #colander{}.

Meanwhile, trim the root and dark green leafy part from the @leek{1} and discard. Halve lengthways, then thinly slice.

Trim the @carrot{1}, then quarter lengthways (no need to peel). Chop widthways into small pieces.

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{40%g}.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the leek and carrot and stir-fry until softened, ~{6-7%minutes}, then stir in the garlic and cook for ~{1%minute} more.

Add the @plain flour{1%tbsp} to the pan. Stir into the veg and cook for ~{1%minute}, then pour in the @water{300%ml} for the sauce and @vegetable stock paste{20%g}.

Bring to the boil, then reduce the heat to medium cook, stirring occasionally, until the liquid has thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Once thickened, stir the @wholegrain mustard{34%g}, @creme fraiche{75%g} and cheese into the sauce.

Remove from the heat and gently stir in the cooked potatoes. Taste and add @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed, adding a splash of water too if it's thickened too much.

== Assembling the Pie ==

Once the pie filling is cooked, transfer it to an appropriately sized #pie dish{}. Cover with the pastry, pressing it over the side of the dish or just sitting it on top, then trimming off any excess.

Make a small hole in the middle to allow steam to escape.

> TIP: Brush the pastry with a little milk if you have some.

Bake your pie on the top shelf of your oven until golden brown, ~{15-20%minutes}. Meanwhile, wipe out the (now empty) frying pan.

== Sauteed Peas ==

When the pie is almost ready, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in the frying pan on medium-high heat. Once hot, add the @peas{120%g} and stir-fry for ~{2-3%minutes}.

Once the pie is out of the oven, allow it to stand for ~{2%minutes} before sharing between your #bowls{}.

Serve with the peas alongside. Enjoy!